# Planning target resolution

**On-demand rule.** Mission Control warm-up loads [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/bootstrap.mdc`](bootstrap.mdc) as the sole R&D `alwaysApply: true` bootstrap. Read **this file** when you need to resolve `.plan.md` targets, snapshot tables, and planning depth-first gates — not on every dispatch warm-up.

Planning protocol branches act on a specific `.plan.md` under the **`.sedea/operations/`** union. The target is resolved from **session input, chat context, and structured choices** — not from the IDE focused-file list alone (IDE state can drift from planning intent).

## Sedea input channel (planning picks)

When a turn **requires a user reply** before you continue (pick a planning branch, confirm a target plan, choose list index **N** for **`new-plan`**), collect that pick through **AskQuestion** per [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc). **Supersedes** the former *AskQuestion or numbered bullet list* option in this rule. Mission Control **AskQuestion** also exposes **free-form text** on the modal — use it for extra instruction alongside an `option` pick; do not reopen choices in prose chat.

**Snapshot table.** The *Next viable moves* column may use **numbered rows** so the developer can read the plan tree in one glance. Those numbers are **reference labels** for the snapshot — offer the same moves as **AskQuestion** `options` on **every** turn (§ above).

**Recap and structured choice.** When the snapshot is long, follow [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc) § **Context and structured choice** and **`../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`** § *Recap, structured choice, act*: **required on every turn** — **AskQuestion tool** or **`MC_PHASED_RESPONSE_V1`** (`display.markdown` = snapshot; `askQuestion` = one `option` per move, brief `label`, branch + target in `prompt` when needed). **Forbidden:** recap-only turn without a modal. Split per rule **2** priority **3** only when impractical — then the **next** message must be phased sentinel-first.

## At a glance — planning vs ship (read first)

| You are on… | Signal that fired | Safe next step | Do **not** |
|-------------|-------------------|----------------|------------|
| **`pr-plan`** on **planning child lane** (`planner`, **`phase-planner`**, Quick Fix Plan agent) | `readyForImplementation: true` | Offer **AskQuestion** **Start coding session** on **that lane** → inline **`pr-plan`** §5d spawns **`coding-session`** | Open worktree on **`pr-plan`** lane, redirect spawn to Squad Leader, or set §8 `phase` past `not-started` from planning outputs alone |
| **`coding-session`** after **`pr-plan`** §5d spawn | `planningHandoffApproved: true` + exit 1 + `EXPECTED_SECTIONS_5_8_TBD` or exit 0 (`OK`) | **Auto-authorize** — open worktree and implement; fill §§5–8 on this lane (no second modal) | Treat `INCOMPLETE` as planning failure; re-ask planning approval |
| **`coding-session`** (detached) | `plan-ws-completeness.mjs` exit 0 or override in worktree-open gate | Proceed with worktree + implementation | Assume planning handoff alone was enough |
| **`coding-session`** (detached) | `developerApprovedImplementation: true` | Continue ship chain; re-emit terminal with §8 `outputs` for host sync | Assume §8 updated without terminal `outputs` |
| **`coding-session`** after inline **`pr-review`** | PR comment triage finished on the coding lane | Re-emit **`coding-session`** terminal with `shipPhase: pr-review` | Assume host sync ran without re-emit |
| Squad Leader **`plan and deliver`** dispatch | Host-sync message parsed | Refresh §8 rows; then resolution gates | Close dispatch **`resolved`** while rows `open`/`blocked` without host sync — **`plan.mdc`** §8 *§8 troubleshooting* |

**Lane rule:** Planning skills (**`pr-plan`**, **`planner`**, decomposition tree) ≠ ship skills (**`coding-session`** → **`pre-pr-review`** → **`create-pr`** → …). **`pr-plan`** may spawn **`coding-session`** on a child lane (§5d); worktrees and implementation stay on the child.

## §8 ship ledger and inline `pr-review`

Squad Leader **§8** on the **`plan and deliver`** dispatch is updated **only** from Mission Control **host sync** on ship child terminals — not from silence on a detached coding lane and **not** from manual recap paste.

| Source | Host sync? | Leader §8 action |
|--------|------------|------------------|
| **`coding-session`**, **`pre-pr-review`**, **`worktree-bootstrap`**, **`create-pr`**, **`deploy-walk`**, **`plan-reconcile`** child terminal with `outputs.targetPlanPath` and derivable `shipPhase` | **Yes** | Parse silent **`Mission Control: ship-ledger sync (section 8).`** — **`plan.mdc`** §8 |
| **`pr-review`** (inline on **`coding-session`**) | Via **`coding-session`** re-emit | **`coding-session`** **must** re-emit with `shipPhase: pr-review` after triage — **`pr-review/SKILL.md`** § *§8 host sync (via coding-session)* |

Do not report §8 as up to date, or propose dispatch **`resolved`**, because **`pr-review`** finished on a coding lane without a subsequent **`coding-session`** terminal that includes §8 **`outputs`**.

